es%20companies%20on%20economic%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20business%20today%2C%20you%20have%20to%20think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20multi-stakeholder%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahlhoff%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20your%20customers%2C%20your%20employees%2C%20your%20investors%2C%20the%20government%2C%20the%20president%2C%20the%20media%2C%20and%20your%20supplier%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tariffs%20are%20part%20of%20Trump's%20economic%20agenda%20to%20bring%20back%20offshored%20American%20manufacturing%20and%20incentivize%20companies%20to%20make%20goods%20domestically%20by%20making%20imports%20more%20costly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBusinesses%20large%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20small%20have%20said%20they%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusinesses-are-labeling-tariff-costs-on-receipts-bid-for-survival-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edisclosing%20tariff%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20means%20to%20retain%20consumer%20trust%2C%20but%20major%20companies%20that%20have%20been%20explicit%20about%20tariff%20costs%20or%20have%20been%20suspected%20of%20such%20plans%20are%20facing%20increasing%20political%20pressure%2C%20often%20from%20the%20president%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-tariff-raise-prices-retail-trump-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWalmart%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20during%20an%20earnings%20call%20on%20May%2015%20that%20they%20would%20need%20to%20raise%20prices%20due%20to%20Trump's%20tariffs.%20In%20a%20post%20on%20Truth%20Social%20on%20May%2017%2C%20Trump%20criticized%20Walmart%20for%20%26quot%3Bblaming%26quot%3B%20his%20policies%20and%20demanded%20that%20the%20retailer%20%26quot%3Beat%20the%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20he%20will%20%26quot%3Bbe%20watching%26quot%3B%20for%20price%20hikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comments%2C%20but%20a%20spokesperson%20previous%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20has%20always%20worked%20to%20keep%20prices%20%26quot%3Bas%20low%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20first%20time%20Trump%20took%20tariff%20price%20hikes%20personally.%20When%20it%20was%20reported%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tariff-costs-trump-schumer-mtg-response-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20considering%20displaying%20how%20much%20tariffs%20are%20contributing%20to%20the%20price%20of%20individual%20products%2C%20the%20White%20House%20press%20secretary%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkaroline-leavitt-white-house-press-secretary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EKaroline%20Leavitt%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20the%20idea%20a%20%26quot%3Bhostile%20and%20political%20act.%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20quickly%20denied%20ever%20planning%20to%20display%20tariff%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSaying%20'tariff'%20could%20be%20interpreted%20as%20a%20political%20statement%20because%20this%20country%20is%20politically%20very%20divided%2C%20so%20it%20is%20a%20very%20complex%20environment%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20terms%20that%20might%20divide%20people%20or%20might%20not%20be%20universally%20liked%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahlhoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20may%20avoid%20the%20issue%20altogether%2C%20and%20instead%20leave%20the%20consumers%20to%20do%20the%20math%2C%20Michael%20Baker%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20at%20D.A.%20Davidson%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-tariff-raise-prices-retail-trump-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetailers%20will%20have%20learned%20they%2