trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-to-protect-your-business-from-these-5-common-risks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwo-female-ceo-paving-the-way-for-future-entrepreneurs-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebarriers%20that%20women%20face%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20starting%20their%20own%20businesses%2C%20many%20are%20choosing%20entrepreneurship%20because%20of%20the%20independence%20and%20autonomy%20it%20can%20offer%2C%20said%20Nich%20Tremper%2C%20senior%20economist%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-hr-tech-startup-gusto-won-over-investors-small-businesses-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGusto%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20seeing%20a%20shift%20from%20this%20necessity%20entrepreneurship%20to%20this%20opportunity%20entrepreneurship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tremper%2C%20referencing%20a%20change%20he%20saw%20in%202022.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we've%20seen%20women%20go%20from%20saying%2C%20'I%20need%20to%20start%20a%20business%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20to%20take%20care%20of%20my%20kids%2C'%20to%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20start%20a%20business%20because%20of%20the%20benefits%20that%20it%20provides.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20growth%20of%20women-owned%20businesses%2C%20barriers%20still%20exist%20for%20women%20seeking%20investments%20to%20start%20or%20scale%20their%20startups.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20many%20rely%20on%20financing%20from%20their%20personal%20networks%20and%20debt%20to%20launch%20their%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255994a15-a9aa-4162-87bd-5d7fb1108f21%5C%22%3EWomen%20of%20color%20are%20driving%20entrepreneurship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETremper%20said%20the%20growth%20of%20new%20businesses%20is%20driven%20by%20women%20of%20color%20who%20are%20seeking%20more%20independence%20and%20ownership%20of%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty-four%20percent%20of%20all%20new%20AAPI-%20and%20Black-owned%20businesses%20were%20started%20by%20women%2C%20compared%20to%2046%25%20that%20were%20started%20by%20their%20male%20colleagues%2C%20per%20Gusto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20justice%20movements%20like%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20and%20Stop%20AAPI%20Hate%20bolstered%20support%20for%20businesses%20owned%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-entrepreneurs-outpacing-men-small-business-barriers-persist-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20of%20color%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20a%20report%20published%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20Wells%20Fargo.%20Tremper%20added%20that%20Black%20and%20AAPI%20women-owned%20businesses%20gained%20more%20momentum%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Hispanic%20women%20made%20up%2043%25%20of%20new%20business%20owners%20compared%20to%2056%25%20of%20Hispanic%20men.%20Gusto%20reported%20that%20the%20disparity%20was%20because%20women-owned%20businesses%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20community%20and%20personal%20services%20sectors%2C%20while%20almost%20half%20of%20all%20Hispanic-owned%20businesses%20are%20concentrated%20in%20goods%20production%20like%20home%20remodeling%20or%20construction.%20Men%20started%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20businesses%20in%20that%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20generations%20of%20women%20are%20also%20reaching%20gender%20parity%3A%20More%20than%20half%20of%20the%20businesses%20created%20by%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20women-owned.%20On%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20male%20baby%20boomers%20made%20up%2064%25%20of%20new%20business%20owners%20compared%20to%2036%25%20of%20boomer%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it's%20typical%20for%20people%20to%20launch%20businesses%20in%20their%20mid-%20to%20late%2030s%20and%20early%2040s%20%E2%80%94%20after%20they've%20developed%20an%20expertise%20in%20a%20particular%20field%20%E2%80%94%20that%20trend%20has%20been%20changing%2C%20Tremper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20women%20are%20increasingly%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20over%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20women%20are%20really%20starting%20businesses%20at%20higher%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20Tremper%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aceca579-8575-474f-b194-ccf9c343e495%5C%22%3EThe%20equity%20gap%20in%20business%20financing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fpublications%2F2018%2Fwhy-women-owned-startups-are-better-bet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen-owned%20businesses%20earn%20a%20higher%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20%240.78%20for%20every%20dollar%20invested%20compared%20to%20men's%20%240.31%2C%20Tremper%20said.%20Additionally%2C%20women-owned%20businesses%20have%20seen%20faster%20revenue%20and%20employment%20growth%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%20compared%20to%20businesses%20started%20by%20men%2C%20per%20Wells%20Fargo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Tremper%20said%20there's%20a%20persistent%20gender%20gap%20between%20equity%20financing%20for%20women%20and%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20women%20who%20do%20receive%20this%20equity%20financing%20really%20outperform%20men%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20getting%20it%20at%20a%20lower%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20Tremper%20said.%20Women%20who%20apply%20for%20private%20investments%20are%2075%25%20less%20likely%20to%20receive%20equity%20funding%20than%20their%20male%20peers%2C%20per%20Gusto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGusto's%20research%20found%20that%20women%20largely%20relied%20on%20their%20social%20networks%20and%20accruing%20personal%20debt%20to%20finance%20their%20new%20businesses.%20It%20was%20more%20common%20for%20women%20to%20also%20secure%20private%20loans%20through%20collateral%20in%20their%20homes%20or%20vehicles%2C%20which%20can%20expose%20them%20to%20more%20financial%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20the%20stakes%20can%20be%20higher%20for%20women-owned%20businesses%E2%80%94if%20the%20founders%20fail%2C%20their%20personal%20finances%20could%20take%20a%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20challenges%20and%20barriers%2C%20women-owned%20businesses%20are%20resilient%20and%20continuing%20to%20find%20success%20in%20the%20market%2C%20Tremper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20these%20women-owned%20businesses%20coming%20into%20the%20economy%20and%20sticking%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20keeping%20their%20course%2C%20they're%20active%20players%20in%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20taking%20on%20personal%20debt%20to%20start%20your%20own%20business%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajdeng%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejdeng%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-started-more-businesses-than-men-used-debt-financing-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747987621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f5e1f6ffb6822ec613fa0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-started-more-businesses-than-men-used-debt-financing-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Women-owned%20startups%20made%20up%20almost%20half%20of%20all%20new%20businesses%20in%202024%2C%20a%2069%25%20increase%20from%202019%2C%20per%20a%20new%20report%20from%20Gusto.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jdeng%40insider.com%20(Jireh%20Deng)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-started-more-businesses-than-men-used-debt-financing-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Israel%20Gets%20Staunch%20Support%20From%20Central%2C%20Eastern%20Europe%22%2C%22content%2