l%2C%20I%20wrote%20about%20a%20federal%20worker%20who%20was%20five%20months%20shy%20of%20eligibility%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-layoffs-federal-workers-pension-plans-retirement-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull%20pension%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%246%2C000%20a%20month%20when%20she%20was%20fired%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnumber-workers-fired-doge-trump-musk-challenger-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDOGE%3C%2Fa%3E%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20nearly%20100%20emails%20from%20readers%2C%20and%20almost%20all%20expressed%20how%20little%20sympathy%20they%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20the%20real%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20several%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGo%20get%20a%20job%20and%20work%20till%20you're%20dead%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNational%20Steel%20went%20bankrupt.%20US%20Steel%20bought%20them%20for%20nothing.%20Thousands%20lost%20what%20was%20promised%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20not%20everyone%20feels%20this%20way.%20I%20tend%20to%20get%20more%20emails%20from%20people%20with%20negative%20responses%20to%20stories%20than%20from%20those%20who%20aren't%20bothered.%20But%20I%20was%20curious%20to%20learn%20more%2C%20so%20I%20spoke%20with%20six%20of%20the%20people%20who%20were%20critical%20of%20the%20federal%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20over%2060%20and%20lived%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-moved-california-new-mexico-buy-home-cleaner-air-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nevada%2C%20Indiana%2C%20Ohio%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpennsylvania-election-results-trump-harris-blue-wall-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPennsylvania%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Maryland.%20Four%20were%20retired%2C%20and%20most%20lived%20on%20fixed%20incomes%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20pension%20the%20subject%20of%20my%20story%20would%20have%20received.%20They%20all%20said%20they%20didn't%20want%20their%20tax%20dollars%20to%20pay%20for%20high%20salaries%20and%20generous%20benefits%20for%20certain%20government%20employees%20when%20private%20sector%20workers%20aren't%20afforded%20the%20same%20rewards.%20They%20also%20questioned%20whether%20some%20government%20jobs%20were%20needed%20at%20all.%20All%20but%20one%20voted%20for%20now-President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20this%20past%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20news%20of%20federal%20firings%20has%20slowed%20down%2C%20DOGE's%20purging%20of%20the%20government%20workforce%20is%20not%20over.%20The%20cuts%20happening%20now%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-leaving-doge-firings-rifs-trump-federal-workforce-cuts-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20permanent%20and%20methodical%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20planning%20to%20reclassify%20some%20workers%20to%20make%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felizabeth-warren-social-security-worker-reclassification-politicize-doge-firings-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeasier%20to%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20six%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20said%20what%20DOGE%20is%20doing%20to%20the%20federal%20workforce%20is%20par%20for%20the%20course%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20Several%20had%20lost%20their%20pensions%20because%20their%20employers%20went%20bankrupt%20or%20stopped%20paying%20into%20them%20and%20switched%20to%20the%20less-generous%20401(k)%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeslie%20Swor%2C%2070%2C%20retired%20seven%20years%20ago%20after%20a%20career%20in%20the%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20an%20independent%20securities%20regulator%20now%20known%20as%20FINRA%2C%20and%20then%20Oracle.%20To%20supplement%20her%20income%2C%20Swor%20works%20a%20contract%20job%20as%20a%20school%20crossing%20guard%20in%20East%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California.%20She%20told%20me%20public%20sector%20workers%20shouldn't%20expect%20to%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bhefty%26quot%3B%20pension%20for%20life.%20After%20all%2C%20private%20sector%20workers%20don't%20take%20that%20as%20a%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwor%20said%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Bfabulous%20benefits%20and%20annual%20raises%20and%20bonuses%26quot%3B%20early%20in%20her%20career%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20In%202007%2C%20when%20she%20became%20an%20administrative%20assistant%20at%20Oracle%2C%20those%20benefits%20were%20no%20longer%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20for%20us%20out%20here%20in%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20in%20my%20experience%2C%20seemed%20to%20get%20much%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20Swor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b39b031-3995-426c-ac8e-4dae189c8d88%5C%22%3EThey%20think%20federal%20salaries%20and%20benefits%20are%20overly%20generous%20compared%20with%20the%20private%20sector%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20readers%20I%20spoke%20with%20were%20surprised%20that%20the%20subject%20of%20my%20story%2C%20Katherine%20Ann%20Reniers%2C%20was%20making%20so%20much%20money%20in%20a%20government%20job%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20generous%20benefits%2C%20and%20said%20the%20private%20sector%20had%20not%20been%20as%20cushy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReniers%2C%20a%20fired%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%20worker%2C%20earned%20a%20base%20salary%20of%20%24177%2C000.%20In%20addition%20to%20a%20pension%2C%20she%20and%20other%20federal%20workers%20have%20the%20Thrift%20Savings%20Plan%2C%20which%20is%20similar%20to%20a%20401(k).%20In%20that%20plan%2C%20the%20government%20matches%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20an%20employee's%20contributions.%20Reniers%20would%20have%20qualified%20for%20federal%20health%20insurance%20for%20life%20if%20she%20had%20hit%20two%20decades%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20Reniers%20took%20a%20pay%20cut%20to%20leave%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20dropping%20from%20%24150%2C000%20to%20%2454%2C000%20in%20annual%20pay%20to%20get%20on%20a%20path%20that%20she%20saw%20as%20stabler%20for%20her%20family%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20At%20first%2C%20she%20moved%20every%20two%20to%20four%20years%2C%20sometimes%20to%20countries%20that%20had%20high%20rates%20of%20violent%20crime%20and%20lacked%20decent%20healthcare.%20In%202010%2C%20she%20was%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20assigned%20to%20Haiti%20after%20a%20devastating%20earthquake.%20Reniers%2C%20now%2053%2C%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%20to%20become%20a%20USAID%20division%20chief%20and%20lives%20in%20Maryland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwor%20said%20her%20perception%20of%20federal%20employees%20was%20that%20they%20traded%20higher%20private%20sector%20salaries%20for%20more%20stability%20and%20better%20benefits.%20That's%20largely%20true%20for%20federal%20workers%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20above.%20A%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20analysis%20of%20fiscal%202022%20data%20found%20that%20federal%20workers%20who%20graduated%20from%20college%20had%20lower%20salaries%20but%20better%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20including%20health%20insurance%2C%20retirement%2C%20and%20paid%20leave%20%E2%80%94%20than%20their%20counterparts%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20Public%20sector%20jobs%20also%20tend%20to%20be%20held%20by%20white-collar%2C%20highly%20educated%20professionals.%20Reniers%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20a%20master's%20degree%2C%20speaks%20four%20languages%2C%20and%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20experience%20in%20Africa%20and%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20workers%20with%20only%20a%20high%20school%20education%2C%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20on%20average%2C%20offers%20better%20pay%20and%20benefits%20than%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FetRDZ%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22federal%20vs%20private%20compensation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Knouse%2C%20a%2062-year-old%20landscaper%20from%20Maryland%2C%20was%20also%20frustrated%20by%20what%20he%20viewed%20as%20generous%20public%20sector%20compensation.%20He's%20worked%20for%2040%20years%20at%20private%20companies%20but%20said%20he%20never%20had%20a%20pension%20or%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%20of%20paid%20vacation.%20His%20current%20employer%20doesn't%20offer%20a%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalaries%20and%20benefits%20for%202%20million%20federal%20employees%2C%20including%20military%20and%20civilian%20personnel%2C%20accounted%20for%20about%204.3%25%20of%20the%20nation's%20%246.8%20trillion%20in%20annual%20spending%20in%20fiscal%202024.%20According%20to%20the%20CBO%2C%20social%20safety%20net%20programs%20like%20Social%20Security%2C%20Medicare%2C%20Medicaid%2C%20nutrition%20assistance%2C%20and%20benefits%20for%20veterans%20and%20military%20personnel%20account%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fpublication%2F61182%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20DOGE%20does%20find%20savings%2C%20Knouse%20would%20like%20to%20see%20lower%20taxes%2C%20better%20healthcare%20for%20retirees%2C%20and%20more%20Social%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20hoping%20that%20he%20could%20also%20cut%20the%20pay%20scale%20for%20federal%20employees%2C%20or%20any%20future%20hiring%20by%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20because%20it's%20got%20to%20balance%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Knouse%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Trump%20and%20the%20DOGE%20office's%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227cbc81b6-21b3-4042-a38a-02fd0f91d165%5C%22%3ESome%20questioned%20whether%20tax%20money%20should%20pay%20for%20pensions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20full-time%20federal%20workers%20can%20start%20receiving%20their%20full%20pension%20once%20they%20hit%20the%20minimum%20retirement%20age%20of%2062.%20Those%20who've%20worked%20two%20decades%20or%20more%20for%20the%20federal%20government%20can%20retire%20earlier.%20Foreign%20service%20officers%20at%20USAID%20and%20the%20State%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20law%20enforcement%20officers%2C%20firefighters%2C%20and%20air%20traffic%20controllers%20%E2%80%94%20can%20retire%20after%2020%20years%20and%20qualify%20for%20larger%20pension%20payouts%20after%20hitting%20that%20anniversary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20the%20people%20I%20interviewed%20how%20they%20viewed%20federal%20pensions%20and%20whether%20they%20wished%20the%20private%20sector%20still%20offered%20them.%20These%20%26quot%3Bdefined%20benefit%20plans%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20guarantee%20a%20certain%20payout%2C%20have%20become%20less%20common%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20as%20employers%20have%20adopted%20more%20%26quot%3Bdefined%20contribution%20plans%26quot%3B%20like%20401(k)s%20or%20employee%20stock%20ownership%2C%20which%20offer%20varying%20payouts%20based%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FkmzmM%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ESwor%2C%20for%20her%20part%2C%20was%20OK%20with%20pensions%20being%20eliminated%20in%20both%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20might%20be%20waking%20up%20that%20this%20is%20our%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Swor%20said%20of%20federal%20pensions.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20not%20just%20receive%20Social%20Security%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Myers%2C%20a%2067-year-old%20retired%20commercial%20real%20estate%20developer%20in%20Nevada%2C%20felt%20conflicted%20about%20the%20federal%20pension%20system.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20he%20understood%20that%20the%20government%20has%20to%20provide%20good%20benefits%20to%20attract%20talent.%20But%20it%20seemed%20overly%20cushy%20to%20him%20that%20certain%20workers%20could%20retire%20with%20a%20full%20pension%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20even%20at%2045%20if%20they%20entered%20the%20government%20young%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20and%20go%20on%20to%20have%20another%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20he%20said%20he%20understood%20a%20pension%20like%20this%20for%20military%20or%20law%20enforcement%20officers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20someone%20like%20Reniers%2C%20who%20had%20to%20move%20around%20a%20lot%20overseas%20at%20the%20government's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%2020%20years%2C%20you've%20probably%20paid%20your%20dues%2C%26quot%3B%20Myers%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20someone%20with%20a%20desk%20job%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20joked%20with%20his%20friends%20that%20there%20would%20be%20a%20revolution%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20not%20rich%20versus%20poor%20but%20public%20sector%20versus%20private%20sector%2C%20because%20workers%20in%20the%20latter%20category%20arriving%20at%20retirement%20age%20will%20be%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20they%20have%20all%20this%20extra%20money%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206ef3acc-b508-4c4c-b70f-81a57d974d5e%5C%22%3EThey%20asked%20whether%20the%20US%20needs%20all%20the%20current%20government%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20didn't%20completely%20agree%20with%20the%20way%20the%20Elon%20Musk-linked%20DOGE%20office%20was%20implementing%20the%20cuts%2C%20the%20pursuit%20of%20finding%20and%20eliminating%20government%20waste%20appealed%20to%20them.%20So%20did%20Trump's%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20mantra%2C%20which%20partly%20explained%20their%20skepticism%20of%20USAID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECynthia%20Bean%2C%20a%2064-year-old%20from%20Indiana%2C%20said%20she%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20the%20agency%20and%20didn't%20understand%20why%20%26quot%3Bbillions%20of%20our%20tax%20dollars%20are%20being%20funneled%20through%20it%20to%20nonprofits%20in%20other%20countries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBean%2C%20who%20owned%20a%20real%20estate%20title%20business%20for%2020%20years%2C%20said%20she%20voted%20for%20Trump%20because%20he%20talked%20about%20running%20the%20US%20government%20like%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20didn't%20have%20a%20problem%20helping%20other%20countries%20prevent%20and%20treat%20HIV%2FAIDS%20or%20other%20diseases.%20People%20also%20need%20water%20and%20power%2C%20she%20added.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarco-rubio-announces-official-end-of-most-usaid-programs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E83%25%20of%20USAID%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20those%20that%20invested%20in%20disease%20prevention%20and%20clean%20water%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafrica.businessinsider.com%2Flocal%2Flifestyle%2Fsouth-africa-grapples-with-hiv-funding-crisis-after-us-aid-cutoff%2F574jblt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoyce%20Weaver%2C%20an%2080-year-old%20senior%20home%20care%20aide%20in%20Pennsylvania%20and%20a%20Democrat%20who%20voted%20for%20then-Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20said%20the%20government%20may%20be%20overspending%20on%20millions%20of%20federal%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20Trump%20is%20doing%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20but%20not%20with%20so%20much%20pain%20for%20so%20many%20and%20so%20much%20danger%20for%20the%20whole%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Weaver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20criticism%20of%20federal%20workers%2C%20including%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Bcrooked%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdishonest%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Musk's%20suggestion%20that%20some%20government%20roles%20are%20%26quot%3Bfake%20jobs%26quot%3B%20resonated%20with%20several%20of%20the%20people%20I%20interviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20need