icate%20one%20of%20Ukraine's%20largest%20coordinated%20drone%20attacks%20on%20Russian%20soil%20since%20the%20war%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20new%20record%20for%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Ukrainian%20analyst%20Petro%20Andryushchenko%20on%20his%20Telegram%20channel.%20%26quot%3BThe%20longest-running%20attack%20by%20Ukrainian%20UAVs%2C%20which%20began%20around%2011%20p.m.%20on%20May%2019%20and%20lasted%20until%204%20a.m.%20on%20May%2022.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exact%20extent%20of%20the%20damage%20caused%20is%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b9e4d6b-0322-42bf-80d6-4ffde519f969%5C%22%3EHow%20Ukraine%20is%20hitting%20Russia%20from%20long%20range%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20description%20of%20the%20drones%20as%20%26quot%3Baircraft-type%26quot%3B%20also%20indicates%20that%20these%20aren't%20the%20typical%20first-person-view%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems%20used%20as%20attack%20drones%20in%20the%20war.%20Such%20drones%20are%20likely%20too%20short-ranged%20to%20reach%20regions%20such%20as%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-struggling-with-ukraine-cessna-style-drone-flying-brick-bomb-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esmall%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20resemble%20the%20Cessna%20propeller%20plane%20and%2C%20while%20laden%20with%20explosives%2C%20are%20meant%20to%20fly%20directly%20into%20targets%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow's%20traditional%20air%20defense%20systems%20have%20reportedly%20struggled%20to%20reliably%20take%20down%20these%20long-range%20drones%2C%20which%20fly%20at%20a%20maximum%20speed%20of%20130%20mph%2C%20much%20slower%20than%20a%20typical%20cruise%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20reports%20this%20week%20suggested%20that%20some%20of%20the%20drones%20struck%20their%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Khinshtein%2C%20the%20acting%20governor%20of%20Kursk%2C%20wrote