ess%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic's%20safety%20report%20comes%20as%20researchers%20and%20top%20execs%20worry%20about%20the%20risks%20of%20advanced%20AI%20models%20and%20their%20intelligent%20reasoning%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-ai-pause-openai-gpt4-powerful-development-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20and%20AI%20experts%20signed%20an%20open%20letter%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecalling%20for%20a%20six-month%20pause%20on%20advanced%20AI%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20said%20powerful%20AI%20systems%20should%20only%20be%20developed%20%26quot%3Bonce%20we%20are%20confident%20that%20their%20effects%20will%20be%20positive%20and%20their%20risks%20will%20be%20manageable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-says-ai-risks-are-being-overlooked-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%20CEO%2C%20Dario%20Amodei%2C%20said%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20the%20benefits%20of%20AI%20are%20big%2C%20so%20are%20the%20risks%2C%20including%20misuse%20by%20bad%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22589389d3-69ed-412e-8701-818b0695468e%5C%22%3EOpus%204%20might%20snitch%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Opus%204%20thinks%20you're%20doing%20something%20seriously%20shady%2C%20it%20might%20report%20you%20to%20the%20authorities%20and%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20placed%20in%20scenarios%20that%20involve%20egregious%20wrongdoing%20by%20its%20users%2C%20given%20access%20to%20a%20command%20line%2C%20and%20told%20something%20in%20the%20system%20prompt%20like%20'take%20initiative%2C'%20it%20will%20frequently%20take%20very%20bold%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20Anthropic%20wrote%20in%20Thursday's%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20locking%20users%20out%20of%20systems%20or%20bulk-emailing%20media%20and%20law%20enforcement%2C%20the%20company%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eadded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Anthropic%20said%20whistleblowing%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20in%20principle%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20warned%20that%20this%20behaviour%20could%20backfire%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20Claude%20is%20fed%20%26quot%3Bincomplete%20or%20misleading%20information%26quot%3B%20and%20prompted%20in%20these%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20observed%20similar%2C%20if%20somewhat%20less%20extreme%2C%20actions%20in%20response%20to%20subtler%20system%20prompts%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Opus%204%20is%20more%20prone%20to%20this%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bhigh-agency%20behaviour%26quot%3B%20than%20earlier%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee32591b-9774-4ae5-b485-0303aa311e01%5C%22%3EAI%20models%20showing%20unsettling%20behaviour%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20agents%20are%20getting%20better%20at%20outsmarting%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20paper%20published%20in%20December%20by%20AI%20safety%20nonprofit%20Apollo%20Research%20found%20that%20AI%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20including%20OpenAI's%20o1%2C%20Google%20DeepMind's%20Gemini%201.5%20Pro%2C%20and%20Meta's%20Llama%203.1%20405B%20%E2%80%94%20are%20capable%20of%20deceptive%20behavior%20to%20achieve%20their%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20found%20the%20systems%20could%20subtly%20insert%20wrong%20answers%2C%20disable%20oversight%20mechanisms%2C%20and%20even%20smuggle%20what%20they%20believe%20to%20be%20their%20own%20model%20weights%20to%20external%20servers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lying%20isn't%20just%20a%20one-off.%20When%20o1%20is%20engaged%20in%20scheming%2C%20it%20%26quot%3Bmaintains%20its%20deception%20in%20over%2085%25%20of%20follow-up%20questions%20and%20often%20remains%20deceptive%20in%20multi-turn%20interrogations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsergey-brin-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20cofounder%20Sergey%20Brin%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20an%20epis