%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-us-jobs-investment-2025-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DApple%2520has%2520said%2520it%2520plans%2Cthe%2520tech%2520giant%2520said%2520Monday.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple's%20pledge%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20invest%20%24500%20billion%20domestically%2C%20a%20new%20report%20from%20Wells%20Fargo%20economists%20predicts%20that%20bringing%20back%20offshored%20manufacturing%20jobs%20will%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Buphill%20battle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20aim%20of%20tariffs%20is%20to%20spur%20a%20durable%20rebound%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-masculine-many-manufacturing-jobs-factories-trade-war-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20manufacturing%3C%2Fa%3E%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20Fargo%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20the%20report.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20a%20meaningful%20increase%20in%20factory%20jobs%20does%20not%20appear%20likely%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%20in%20our%20view.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20attributes%20the%20potentially%20low%20factory%20job%20growth%20to%20high%20labor%20costs%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20suitable%20workers%20to%20fill%20vacant%20positions%2C%20and%20a%20subdued%20population%20growth%20from%20lower%20fertility%20rates%20and%20slower%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigher%20prices%20and%20policy%20uncertainty%20may%20weigh%20on%20firms'%20ability%20and%20willingness%20to%20expand%20payrolls%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tariffs%20are%20part%20of%20Trump's%20broader%20economic%20agenda%20to%20revive%20American%20manufacturing%20as%20a%20pathway%20toward%20middle-class%20prosperity.%20The%20tariffs%20are%20meant%20to%20hike%20the%20costs%20of%20imports%20to%20incentivize%20companies%20to%20make%20goods%20domestically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJobs%20and%20factories%20will%20come%20roaring%20back%20into%20our%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20while%20announcing%20tariffs%20on%20April%202.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20ultimately%2C%20more%20production%20at%20home%20will%20mean%20stronger%20competition%20and%20lower%20prices%20for%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20tariffs%20imposed%20on%20April%202%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariff-reversal-scrambling-warehousing-math-importers-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etemporarily%20paused%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20greatly%20reduced%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-90-day-tariff-deal-china-leaves-small-businesses-struggling-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariffs%20on%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%2010%25%20across-the-board%20tariff%20remains%2C%20as%20do%20some%20specific%20tariffs%20on%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%2C%20plus%2030%25%20in%20duties%20on%20China.%20Duties%20at%20their%20current%20level%20are%20still%20the%20highest%20they%20have%20been%20since%20the%201940s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20order%20for%20manufacturing%20employment%20to%20return%20to%20its%20historic%20peak%2C%20we%20estimate%20at%20a%20minimum%20%242.9%20trillion%20in%20net%20new%20capital%20investment%20is%20required%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20Fargo%20analysts%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAssuming%20businesses%20are%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20invest%20such%20ample%20sums%2C%20questions%20over%20staffing%20remain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20bank%20says%20that%20US%20manufacturing%20employment%20currently%20stands%20at%2012.8%20million%2C%20down%20from%20its%201979%20peak%20of%2019.5%20million.%20To%20get%20back%20to%20that%20mark%2C%20the%20US%20would%20need%20to%20add%20roughly%206.7%20million%20jobs.%20Wells%20Fargo%20added%20that%20the%20figure%20is%20nearly%20the%20same%20as%20the%20entire%20pool%20of%20unemployed%20Americans%2C%20which%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApril%20was%207.2%20million%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPopulation%20aging%2C%20negative%20perceptions%2C%20and%20skill%20mismatches%20also%20underpin%20workforce%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20Fargo%20analysts%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNew%20jobs%20will%20require%20different%20skills%20than%20those%20previously%20lost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Taiwanese%20chipmaker%20TSMC%20said%20it%20delayed%20the%20opening%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsmc-arizona-semiconductor-chip-fab-taiwan-china-president-joe-biden-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArizona%20chip%20factory%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20workers.%20A%20report%20released%20in%20April%202024%20by%20Deloitte%20and%20the%20Manufacturing%20Institute%20also%20found%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%203.8%20million%20new%20manufacturing%20jobs%20anticipated%20by%202033%20could%20remain%20unfilled%20due%20to%20skill%20gaps%20and%20other%20population%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20must%20be%20high%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20cost%20of%20domestic%20production%20competitive%20in%20the%20US%20market%2C%20and%20they%20also%20must%20be%20kept%20in%20place%20long%20enough%20for%20producers%20to%20bring%20on%20additional%20workers%20and%20expand%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20concluded.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20economic%20or%20political%20costs%20are%20deemed%20too%20high%2C%20the%20current%20administration%20could%20quickly%20dial-back%20prevailing%20duties%20further.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-wont-bring-manufacturing-jobs-back-wells-fargo-analysts-say-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747967506000%2C%22visual